6:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both QuillBot and Zimmwriter share a solid foundation of core features including . Where QuillBot pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Short Form and Tone Control and Plagiarism Check and Multilingual and Browser Extension, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. On the other hand, Zimmwriter uniquely offers Long Form and Seo Tools and Templates, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, QuillBot holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 9/10, while Zimmwriter scores 7/10 overall and 5/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, QuillBot offers a more budget-friendly entry point at Free, compared to Zimmwriter's starting price of $14/mo. QuillBot has a notable advantage here with its free plan, allowing you to get started without any financial commitment. Zimmwriter does not currently offer a free tier, which means you will need to pay from day one."}]]}]
